    • Method Detail

      • process

        public ImageOutputSet process(ImageInputSet input,
                              boolean isJunction)
        Description copied from class: ImageProc
        Processes the set of five images in the input set. This method blocks and returns the result. Treat as a possibly lengthy method. The returned images are guarenteed to not be in place of the input images, so it is safe to deallocate the input images after this method call.
        Specified by:
        process in class ImageProc
        Parameters:
        input - The input set of five images
        isJunction - if the front image contains a junction (means no headlights will be shown)
        Returns:
        The resulting four images
